    {
      "id": "e45cfc9f-cb41-4ed4-8590-45bec671c737",
      "message": {
        "Role": "assistant",
        "Content": "I'll start by asking clarifying questions to understand exactly what you need before generating any plan.\n\n## Clarifying Questions\n\nA \"golang chatroom\" could mean many different things — let me understand your specific goals:\n\n**1. What type of chatroom are you building?**\n- Terminal/TUI application (like this FlowState project)?\n- Web-based (browser frontend + Go backend)?\n- CLI tool (command-line, no UI)?\n- Something else?\n\n**2. What is the core use case?**\n- Multi-user real-time chat between humans?\n- A single-user chat interface to an AI/LLM?\n- A developer tool (e.g. team chat, IRC-style)?\n- Integration into an existing system?\n\n**3. What is the scope of this chatroom?**\n- Single room vs. multiple named rooms/channels?\n- Public vs. private rooms?\n- Persistent message history or ephemeral (messages lost on disconnect)?\n- User authentication/accounts, or anonymous?\n\n**4. What transport/protocol should it use?**\n- WebSockets?\n- gRPC streaming?\n- TCP sockets?\n- HTTP long-polling?\n- No preference — you want a recommendation?\n\n**5. What does \"done\" look like for you?**\n- A working prototype you can demo?\n- Production-ready with tests?\n- A learning exercise?\n- Something to integrate into FlowState?\n\n**6. Any constraints?**\n- Target Go version?\n- Specific libraries allowed/forbidden (e.g. no frameworks, only stdlib)?\n- Deployment target (local, Docker, cloud)?\n- Timeline?\n\n---\n\nWhat is the primary goal of this chatroom?",
        "ToolCalls": null
      },
      "embedded": false
    },
